laboratory_examinations.findings: Five fluoroscopic images demonstrate cannulation of the common bile duct with at least one irregular filling defect present just distal to the cystic duct insertion within the common bile duct. A second filling defect located more distally is also likely. The visualized portions of the intrahepatic ducts are unremarkable.
Total bilirubin level is 9.4 mg/dL (normal range 8.4 - 10.2 mg/dL), which is within normal limits.
